SIMPLE: particularity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Particularity
<hw>Par*tic`u*lar"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Particularities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>particularit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The state or quality of being particular; distinctiveness;
circumstantiality; minuteness in detail.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is particular</def>; as: <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>Peculiar quality; individual characteristic; peculiarity.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧An old heathen altar with this <xex>particularity</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Addison.</au> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Special circumstance; minute detail;
particular.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Even descending to
<xex>particularities</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Sir P. Sidney.</au> <sd>(c)</sd>
<def>Something of special or private concern or interest.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let the general trumpet blow his blast,⟦br⟧
<qex>Particularities</qex> and petty sounds⟦br⟧
To cease!</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Particularization</ent>⟦br⟧
